content:
Update Your Messaging for Web Deployment After Upgrading to Enhanced Domains

To ensure that your Messaging for Web deployment remains active after you enable enhanced domains, republish your deployment. If you use Messaging for Web in an Experience Builder site, update your allowlisted URLs.

Available in: Lightning Experience
This article applies to:	Messaging for Web channels
User Permissions:
Customize Application
Manage Profiles and Permission Sets
Create and Setup Experiences

In Winter ’24, all orgs get enhanced domains and the feature can’t be disabled. For more information, see Enhanced Domains Timeline.

After enhanced domains are deployed, a Messaging for Web deployment that was previously published no longer appears to your customer. Admins must take additional steps to republish all pre-existing deployments. These steps differ between messaging that’s embedded in a third-party website and messaging that’s embedded in an Experience Builder site.

Republish Your Website After Upgrading to Enhanced Domains

After upgrading to enhanced domains, republish any Messaging for Web deployments that are live in your website.
Click the edit button to the right of your deployment, and then select View.
Click Publish.

Republish Your Experience Builder Site After Upgrading to Enhanced Domains

Update the Experience Builder to use the new enhanced domain.
From Setup, click All Sites.
Click Page Structure, and then select Embedded Messaging from the dropdown.
Select the URL presented in the Enhanced Service URL dropdown.
Add the new enhanced service URL to the Trusted URLs list in Setup.

In Experience Builder, highlight and copy the enhanced service URL from the Enhanced Service URL dropdown. 
From Setup, click Trusted URLs, and then select New Trusted URL.
Name it, and paste the copied URL into the URL field.
Select connect-src (scripts).
Save your changes.

Add the new enhanced service URL to the Trusted URLs list for your Experience Builder site.
In Experience Builder, click Settings, and then select Security & Privacy.
Click + Add Trusted Site.
Paste your enhanced service URL into the URL field.
Click Add Site.
Republish your Experience Builder site.
From Setup, click All Sites, and then select Publish.

Update your embedded service deployment to use the new enhanced domain.
Return to the All Sites landing page, and copy the domain portion of the URL for your site.
From Setup, click Embedded Service Deployments, and then click Edit.
Paste the domain you just copied into the Domain field, and then save your changes.
Republish your embedded service deployment.
Click the edit button to the right of your deployment, and then select View.
Click Publish.

Add the new enhanced domain to your CORS allowlist.
From Setup, click CORS, and then click New.
Paste the domain that you previously copied into the Origin URL Pattern field, and then save your changes.
title: Updating Service Cloud Messaging for Web Deployments
